This program crawls Spanish idioms from the Refranero MultingÃ¼e, maintained by the Centro Virtual Cervantes: http://cvc.cervantes.es/lengua/refranero/Default.aspx. The center reserves all rights (reservados todos los derechos), so you likely can only use the data non-commercially.

It outputs only those idioms with Spanish definitions, which are heavily used today ("Muy usado").

Usage:

1. Get link slugs for all idioms:

    refranero-scraper -print-slugs > slugs.txt

2. Parse link slugs, and print out the idioms and definitions. It could take a while to parse these ~2000 pages.

    < slugs.txt | refranero-scraper -read-slugs > idioms_and_definitions.txt

